# DESCRIPTION
# Preview Activity from _Active Calculus_ by Matthew Boelkins
# ENDDESCRIPTION

## DBsubject(Calculus - single variable)
## DBchapter(Differentiation)
## DBsection(Product rule (without trigonometric functions))
## Institution(Westmont College)
## Author(David Hunter)
## Level(3)
## MO(1)
## TitleText1('Active Calculus')
## AuthorText1('Matthew Boelkins')
## EditionText1('2015')
## Section1('2.3')
## Problem1('2 3')
## KEYWORDS('differentiation', 'product rule')

DOCUMENT();
loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "parserPopUp.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

Context("Numeric");
Context()->variables->add(t=>"Real");
$k = random(2,5,1);
$j = random(2,8,1);
$f = Formula("$k*t^2");
$g = Formula("t^3+$j*t");
$df = $f->D('t');
$dg = $g->D('t');
$p = Formula("$k*t^5+$k*$j*t^3")->reduce;
$dp = $p->D('t')->reduce;

$popupF = PopUp(["?", "True", "False"], "False");

TEXT(beginproblem());
Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT
Let \(f\) and \(g\) be the functions defined by \(f(t) = $f\) and \(g(t) = $g\). $PAR

Determine \(f'(t)\) and \(g'(t)\). $BR
\(f'(t) = \) \{ ans_rule(20) \} $BR
\(g'(t) = \) \{ ans_rule(20) \} $BR
$PAR
Let \(p(t) = $f ($g) \) and observe that \(p(t) = f(t) \cdot g(t) \). Rewrite the formula
for \(p\) by distributing the \($f\) term. Then, compute \(p'(t) \) using the sum and constant
multiple rules. $BR
\(p'(t) = \) \{ ans_rule(20) \} $BR
$PAR
True or False: \(p'(t) = f'(t) \cdot g'(t) \)
\{ $popupF->menu() \}
$PAR
END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 0;
ANS($df->cmp() );
ANS( $dg->cmp() );
ANS( $dp->cmp() );
ANS( $popupF->cmp() );

Context()->texStrings;
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR SOLUTION $PAR
Using the differentiation rules gives \(f'(t) = $df\) and \(g'(t)=$dg\). We can rewrite
\(p(t)=$p\), so its derivative is \(p'(t) = $dp\). Notice that \(p'(t) \neq f'(t)\cdot g'(t) \).
END_SOLUTION
Context()->normalStrings;

ENDDOCUMENT();

